The Revanites are a splinter faction of Malak’s Sith Empire. After Revan’s fall, they are those who took issue with Malak’s new, more destructive war, and threw in with Lord Valerius, supporting his rebellion against the Darth and bid to claim the title of Dark Lord of the Sith. For some their loyalty is to Valerius, others to their idea of who Revan was and what he stood for, others simply take issue with Darth Malak, and some still seek out the Revanites for their less despicable tendencies as far as Sith go, seeing them more as the Jedi Crusaders of the late Mandalorian Wars than the monsters that compose the Sith Empire. Regardless, they are still followers of the Dark Side.

The Revanites promote competition amongst their ranks, both among the Force Sensitives among their number and their rank and file troops. Those the most merciless, cruel and powerful amongst them are elevated, while those exhibiting softer tendencies are treated like fodder and find death sooner rather than later - often from friendly fire.

These are the former among them. Clad in finer armor and given access to the newest in Imperial weapons technology as reward for their faithful service to the Sith.

The Sith Assassins, Intelligencia, Inquisitors, or whatever name they adopt on that given day, have a host of responsibilities within the Sith Order. From exploratory missions to uncover more of their lost heritage, to rooting out dissent and spies among the ranks of the Sith, to discovering and exploiting weaknesses in their enemies, the Assassins are highly prized agents of the Empire.

The central spire of the Twilight Praxeum is the heart of the Revanites' space station. It is here where the doors to the hangars, the combat deck, the training deck, and the Chamber of the Convocation, come together. 

At the very center of the central spire stands a towering statue of Revan. Carved as a creature of pride and dignity, he is depicted as anchoring an ancient blade into the floors of the Twilight Praxeum; oft taken as a symbol of the deceased Darth's role as the spiritual leader of the Revanites.

A sarcophagus sits somberly before the statue. Most believe it to be empty, though a few are convinced that the corpse of Revan had been recovered and interred within. The only one who might know for sure is Lord Valerius himself. To disturb the sarcophagus is understood amongst those who dwell within or visit the Twilight Praxeum to be an act of desecration punishable by death, no matter rank or standing.

Around the central spire, vast and titanic generators reach from the lower levels up to the higher tiers and platforms of the space station. The central spire is cavernous, and so bridges and platforms oft span it, while the thrumming of the space station's defensive systems could be felt by those who tread its ground.
